│ stop({"edit_points": [[1120, 1128, "llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.h"]],     │
│ "thoughts": "The user is reporting a crash in the Loop Vectorizer due to an assertion      │
│ failure in `VPlanTransforms::dropPoisonGeneratingRecipes`. The assertion indicates that an │
│ instruction with poison-generating flags is represented by a `VPRecipe` that doesn't       │
│ handle these flags.\n\nThe reproducer involves a call to `@llvm.fabs.f64` with the `nnan`  │
│ flag. The backtrace and my investigation using the debugger confirm that the VPlan recipe  │
│ for this intrinsic call is `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe`. \n\nThe root cause is that            │
│ `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe` does not inherit from `VPRecipeWithIRFlags`, which is the base    │
│ class for recipes that need to manage instruction flags like `nnan`. Consequently, the     │
│ `nnan` flag is not properly tracked in the VPlan, leading to the crash when                │
│ `dropPoisonGeneratingRecipes` tries to process it.\n\nThe fix is to make                   │
│ `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe` inherit from `VPRecipeWithIRFlags` and to update its constructor  │
│ to initialize the base class with the flags from the intrinsic instruction. This will      │
│ ensure that the flags are correctly propagated through the VPlan, allowing the vectorizer  │
│ to handle them appropriately."})                                                           │
