╭─ Assistant [MainThread@2316216] ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ ### 1. Understanding the Issue                                                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The LLVM Loop Vectorizer is crashing with an assertion failure when processing a loop      │
│ containing a call to the `@llvm.fabs.f64` intrinsic with the `nnan` (No NaNs) flag. The    │
│ assertion, `(!Instr || !Instr->hasPoisonGeneratingFlags()) && "found instruction with      │
│ poison generating flags not covered by VPRecipeWithIRFlags"`, is triggered within the      │
│ `VPlanTransforms::dropPoisonGeneratingRecipes` function. This indicates that the VPlan     │
│ recipe created for the `fabs` intrinsic does not properly handle its poison-generating     │
│ `nnan` flag.                                                                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log                                                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The backtrace points directly to the problem. The crash occurs during the VPlan generation │
│ phase of the loop vectorizer. Specifically, the `dropPoisonGeneratingRecipes` utility is   │
│ called to handle recipes that might generate poison values. The `llvm.fabs` call with the  │
│ `nnan` flag is one such instruction. The assertion failure tells us that the VPlan recipe  │
│ representing this call, which is a `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe`, is not equipped to manage     │
│ these flags. It is expected to inherit from `VPRecipeWithIRFlags` to signal its capability │
│ to handle such flags, but it does not.                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 3. Root Cause Analysis                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root cause of the crash is an omission in the class definition of                      │
│ `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe`. In the VPlan infrastructure, recipes that correspond to LLVM IR  │
│ instructions with poison-generating flags (like `nuw`, `nsw`, `nnan`, `ninf`, `fmf`, etc.) │
│ must inherit from the `VPRecipeWithIRFlags` class. This special base class provides the    │
│ necessary interface for the VPlan to track and manage these flags during transformation.   │
│                                                                                            │
│ The `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe` is used to represent intrinsic calls within a VPlan. In the   │
│ provided reproducer, it represents the `call nnan double @llvm.fabs.f64(...)` instruction. │
│ However, the `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe` class was defined to inherit only from               │
│ `VPSingleDefRecipe`, not `VPRecipeWithIRFlags`. Consequently, when                         │
│ `dropPoisonGeneratingRecipes` encounters this recipe, it finds an instruction with a       │
│ poison-generating flag (`nnan`) but a recipe that doesn't claim to handle it, leading to   │
│ the assertion failure.                                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to modify the `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe` class to inherit from                    │
│ `VPRecipeWithIRFlags` and to initialize the base class with the fast-math flags from the   │
│ underlying `CallInst`.                                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                              │
│                                                                                            │
│ The following edit will be made to `llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.h`:       │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```cpp                                                                                     │
│ // llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.h:1120-1128                                │
│ class VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe final                                                         │
│     : public VPRecipeWithIRFlags<VPSingleDefRecipe> {                                      │
│   Intrinsic::ID IntrinID;                                                                  │
│   bool IsScalable;                                                                         │
│                                                                                            │
│ public:                                                                                    │
│   VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe(const CallInst &CI, Intrinsic::ID IID,                            │
│                          ArrayRef<VPValue *> Operands, Type *ResultTy,                     │
│                          const DebugLoc &DL);                                              │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│                                                                                            │
│ This change modifies `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe` to inherit from                              │
│ `VPRecipeWithIRFlags<VPSingleDefRecipe>`.                                                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ The following edit will be made to `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp`:              │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```cpp                                                                                     │
│ // llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp:100-104                                         │
│ VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe::VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe(const CallInst &CI,                         │
│                                                Intrinsic::ID IID,                          │
│                                                ArrayRef<VPValue *> Operands,               │
│                                                Type *ResultTy,                             │
│                                                const DebugLoc &DL)                         │
│     : VPRecipeWithIRFlags(VPRecipeOpcode::VPWidenIntrinsic, &CI, Operands,                 │
│                           ResultTy, CI.getFastMathFlags()),                                │
│       IntrinID(IID), IsScalable(CI.isScalable()) {                                         │
│   setDebugLoc(DL);                                                                         │
│ }                                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│                                                                                            │
│ This change updates the constructor of `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe` to correctly initialize    │
│ the `VPRecipeWithIRFlags` base class by passing the fast-math flags from the `CallInst`.   │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 5. Conclusion                                                                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ By making `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe` inherit from `VPRecipeWithIRFlags` and properly         │
│ initializing it with the instruction's flags, we ensure that the VPlan correctly models    │
│ the semantics of the intrinsic call. This allows the `dropPoisonGeneratingRecipes`         │
│ function and other parts of the vectorizer to correctly handle the `nnan` flag, resolving  │
│ the assertion failure and enabling successful vectorization of the loop.                   │
