│                                                                                            │
│ The reproducer involves a call to `@llvm.fabs.f64` with the `nnan` flag. The backtrace and │
│ my investigation using the debugger confirm that the VPlan recipe for this intrinsic call  │
│ is `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe`.                                                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root cause is that `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe` does not inherit from                      │
│ `VPRecipeWithIRFlags`, which is the base class for recipes that need to manage instruction │
│ flags like `nnan`. Consequently, the `nnan` flag is not properly tracked in the VPlan,     │
│ leading to the crash when `dropPoisonGeneratingRecipes` tries to process it.               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to make `VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe` inherit from `VPRecipeWithIRFlags` and to      │
│ update its constructor to initialize the base class with the flags from the intrinsic      │
│ instruction. This will ensure that the flags are correctly propagated through the VPlan,   │
│ allowing the vectorizer to handle them appropriately.                                      │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                            │
│                                                                                            │
